Sentencas: Electrolytes with high-proton conduction and low activation energy are attractive for reducing the high operating temperature of solid-oxide fuel cells to less than < 600 C-o. In this work, we have fabricated semiconducting electrolyte SrFeTiO3-delta (SFT) material exhibiting high ionic conduction and exceptionally high protonic conduction at low operating temperature but with low electronic conduction to evade the short-circuiting issue.
Titulo: Demonstrating the potential of iron-doped strontium titanate electrolyte with high-performance for low temperature ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The prepared fuel cell device exhibited high open-circuit voltage (OCV) and a highpower output of 534 mW/cm(2), of which 474 mW/cm(2) could be for sure be related to the protonic part.
Titulo: Demonstrating the potential of iron-doped strontium titanate electrolyte with high-performance for low temperature ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The current study suggests that usage of semiconductor SrFeTiO3-delta facilitates a high concentration of oxygen vacancies on the surface of SFT, which mainly benefits proton conduction.
Titulo: Demonstrating the potential of iron-doped strontium titanate electrolyte with high-performance for low temperature ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, lower grain boundary resistance leads to obtain higher performance.
Titulo: Demonstrating the potential of iron-doped strontium titanate electrolyte with high-performance for low temperature ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: Also, the Schottky junction phenomena are proposed to inhibit the e-conduction and excel the ions transportation.
Titulo: Demonstrating the potential of iron-doped strontium titanate electrolyte with high-performance for low temperature ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The high performance and ionic conductivity suggest that SFT could be a promising electrolyte for protonic ceramic fuel cells.
Titulo: Demonstrating the potential of iron-doped strontium titanate electrolyte with high-performance for low temperature ceramic fuel cells
